fix(persistence/sqlite): address review feedback — CHECK constraints, BASE_URL, FK pragma

Address remaining live review threads from CodeRabbit's first round:

Code fixes:
  - Add DB-level CHECK constraints to matches.winner and moves.color so
    the TypeScript Winner / MoveColor unions are enforced at the
    storage boundary too. Raw SQL writes can no longer smuggle invalid
    values through the type-safe repo layer.
  - PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON in src/persistence/sqlite/client.ts after
    every connection open. SQLite docs are explicit that foreign-key
    enforcement is per-connection and OFF by default; capacitor-sqlite
    does not promise to enable it for us. Without this the schema's
    cascade rules don't actually fire at runtime.
  - Resolve game-db.meta.json against import.meta.env.BASE_URL via a
    new resolveMetaUrl() helper (mirrors what jeep-web.ts already does
    for wasmpath). Required for non-root deployments and Capacitor
    file:// builds.
  - Reject malformed user_version values in fetchServedMeta. The old
    typeof === "number" check still accepted NaN, fractional, and
    negative values, which would compute impossible replay windows.
  - Drop the ignored `gameDbUrl` BootstrapOptions field. capacitor-sqlite's
    copyFromAssets() auto-discovers via databases.json; a separate URL
    override doesn't apply on that code path. Documented why in the
    BootstrapOptions docstring.
  - Wire pretest / pretest:watch / pretest:node to run prepare:public
    so any vitest entry point (not just test:browser) gets the
    generated DB metadata + WASM in place.

Schema migration drizzle/0001_add_check_constraints.sql generated by
drizzle-kit. Applies the two CHECK constraints via SQLite's standard
table-rename idiom. public/assets/databases/chonkersSQLite.db rebuilt
at user_version = 2.

69 Node-tier tests + 16 browser-tier tests still pass against the new
two-migration ladder. Typecheck and lint clean.

